The paper deals with the mathematical foundations of rough sets and matroids, which are both topics in discrete mathematics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves combinatorial generalizations, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of set families and approximation operators suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses representations and characteristics of the parametric matroid, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
